author: Adam Loewy
title: Thursday’s prep volleyball results
text:
Thursday’s prep volleyball results Originally published October 15, 2015 at 10:57 pm Updated October 15, 2015 at 10:58 pm The WesCo 3A and 4A conferences dominated the region with Monroe, Lynnwood, and Lake Stevens earning big wins. By Adam Loewy 
Monroe 3, Snohomish 1. 
The Monroe Bearcats improved to a 10-0 overall record, behind senior Jessica Clark’s 13 kills and 23 digs. Freshman Tatum McGovern and senior Alley Haden also combined for 31 assists. Snohomish senior Kyla Mellick finished with a game-high six aces and 10 kills, along with 15 digs. Senior Jessica Brennis and Sophomore Roz Gillie powered the offense for the Panthers, combining for 26 kills.

The Lynnwood Royals and Arlington Eagles combined for 155 digs in a WesCo 3A Royals win. Lynnwood’s Anna Greenwood, Katie Mansfield, Katie Swan, and Reilly Walsh combined for 93 digs . Mansfield finished with a game-high 45 digs, while Swan recorded 22 digs, 39 assists and seven kills. Greenwood had 16 digs and a game-high 12 kills. Arlington’s Ally Peterson and Alyssa Crain each finished with 16 digs. Peterson also recorded 21 assists, four kills, and three blocks, while Morgan Van Laar recorded a team-high 21 digs. 
Lake Stevens 3, Mount Vernon 2. 
Sophomore Lilly Eason had 14 kills, 24 assists, 4 aces, and 4 blocks for Lake Stevens in a five-set, tiebreaker loss to Mount Vernon. On the winning side, senior Amanda Brown had 11 kills and 16 digs. Freshman Abbi Beuckman dished out a game-high 32 assists and Sophomore Kennedy Coulter recorded a double-double with 11 kills and 10 digs.
